---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import HighlightsMasonry from '../components/HighlightsMasonry.astro';
import { getHighlights, getHighlightsByCategory } from '../utils/highlights';

const highlights = await getHighlights();
const highlightsByCategory = await getHighlightsByCategory();
---

<PageLayout
  title="Notes"
  description="This is a season of execution: less narration, more action. I write from real life as a stay-at-home, remote-working father² and stepfather², practicing patience, temperance, and grounded leadership in public."
  path="/"
  structuredDataType="website"
  showTitle={false}
>
  <HighlightsMasonry posts={highlights} postsByCategory={highlightsByCategory} />

  <p class="mt-10 text-[1.06rem] leading-relaxed text-[rgb(var(--color-text-muted))]">
    If those highlights resonate, keep going. Start with context, follow a theme, or read everything
    in sequence.
  </p>
  <ul class="my-6 space-y-2">
    <li>
      <a href="/guided-path" class="text-[rgb(var(--color-primary))] hover:underline"
        ><strong>Start Here (Guided Path)</strong></a
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/category" class="text-[rgb(var(--color-primary))] hover:underline"
        ><strong>Browse by Topic (Categories)</strong></a
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/everything" class="text-[rgb(var(--color-primary))] hover:underline"
        ><strong>Everything (All Posts)</strong></a
      >
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="mt-12">Why this space exists right now</h2>

  <p>
    This space keeps me accountable to what I claim to value. I use it to document the gap between
    what I know and what I actually do, then close that gap in public and in private, even when
    nobody is watching.
  </p>

  <p>
    I also write for fun. This is a valve for pressure, a creative output, and in many ways, art.
    You will still find experiments and unfinished thoughts here. The difference is the standard:
    less performance, more practice.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
